// Data-plane v1 — the tunnel between a customer-VPC data plane and the
// Lantern control-plane.
//
// In the control-plane / data-plane split, the data plane (an agent process
// running inside the customer's VPC — EKS/GKE/AKS or bare host) does NOT
// accept inbound connections from the control-plane. Instead the agent dials
// OUT to the control-plane and holds a long-lived gRPC connection. Over that
// connection it:
//
